page.title: 05SELBY BUS SERVICES
page.content: SELBY HAS FIVE MAIN BUS SERVICES:THE 401 WHICH RUNS EVERY HOUR TO LEEDS FROM GOOLE PASSES THROUGH THE TOWN;THE 405 SERVICE WHICH GOES FROM DONCASTER TO YORK PASSES THROUGH;THE 404 SELBY TO HEMINGBROUGH;THE 400 TOWN SERVICE;THE SELBY TO PONTEFRACT SERVICE. THERE ARE THREE PRIVATELY OPERATED SERVICES:THORNES RUN TO BUBWITH; JARONDA RUN BUSES TO YORK VIA CAWOOD AND ALSO TO THE VILLAGES SOUTH OF SELBY;MOORES OPERATE TO CAWOOD AND RYTHER ON CERTAIN DAYS. THERE IS A SMALL BUS STATION IN SELBY WHICH IS NEAR THE TOWN CENTRE.IT IS ALSO NEAR THE RAILWAY STATION WHICH MEANS THAT IT IS EASY TO TRANSFER FROM ONE FORM OF TRANSPORT TO ANOTHER.
